100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 19, 1925, significant developments unfolded in the world stage. In Britain, the government faced mounting pressure over the coal industry strike, as miners continued their demands for better wages and conditions. Meanwhile, in the United States, the trial of John T. Scopes, known as the "Monkey Trial," stirred national debate over evolution and education, attracting widespread attention. In the Middle East, tensions escalated as nationalist movements gained momentum, particularly in Egypt, challenging colonial powers.
